[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has a balanced hand with 23 points. He opens 2\C and expects to rebid 2NT.

NORTH has 12 points so makes a positive response in her best suit. Since that suit is 
\Ds she must jump to the 3-level. 

SOUTH now describes his balanced, minimum hand by bidding 3NT.

NORTH bids 6NT, knowing that the partnership holds at least 34 points.}

