{SOUTH, with 9 points and a 5-card suit, should make a positive response, 2\S.

NORTH bids her \Hs and SOUTH agrees the trump suit with a 
4\H bid.

NORTH thinks there is a slam, so she invokes Blackwood. Hearing that SOUTH holds two Aces she bids 
6NT. She could also have bid 6\H but 6NT scores a little more.}

